def: The science which treats of the structure and functions of thestomach; a treatise of the stomach.
An instrument for removing wax from the ear.

Proceeding from adulterous intercourse. Hence: Spurious;without the support of law; illegal.When any particular class of artificers or traders thought proper toact as a corporation without a charter, such were called adulterineguilds. Adam Smith.
To take away. [Obs.]Ire . . . benimeth the man fro God. Chaucer.
A cistern or vault at the point where a street gutterdischarges into a sewer, to oatch bulky matters which would not passreadly throught the sewer. Knight.
